covered: Valid Request: Happy path scenarios (TC01) validate correct 200 response and matching accounts when only path parameter provided.
Empty Response: Scenarios for no matches (TC04) and empty database (TC05) verify empty array responses.
Pagination: Offset/limit handling and multi-page behavior covered (TC02, TC03, TC15).
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid/invalid combinations (TC02–TC08, TC14).
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid tokens (TC09, TC10) ensure unauthorized access is handled.
Error Handling: Validation errors for invalid inputs (TC06–TC08) and invalid search key, plus general error scenarios.
Security: SQL injection (TC12) and XSS (TC13) scenarios test input sanitization and error responses.
Edge Cases: Extra/unexpected query parameters ignored (TC14) and backward compatibility with older clients (TC18).
Performance/Volume: Large dataset handling with limit and concurrent requests (TC15).
Timeout/Resilience: Timeout behavior (TC16) and service unavailability in integration/dep scenarios (TC11, TC19).
Regression: Empty searchKey handled (TC17) and backward compatibility (TC18).
Accessibility: Payload structure considerations for screen readers (TC20).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests validating rate limiting or throttling under high request volume.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation.
403 Forbidden coverage: Tests focus on 401 Unauthorized; explicit 403 scenarios are not covered.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under bursty/high load (beyond TC15).
Add tests validating caching headers and cache behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) to satisfy caching guidelines.
Include explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover possible privilege-related access control cases, in addition to 401 tests.
